SIMPLE: two-handed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Two-handed
<hw>Two"-hand`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having two hands; -- often used as an epithet equivalent to
<xex>large</xex>, <xex>stout</xex>, <xex>strong</xex>, or
<xex>powerful</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Two-handed</xex> sway.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Used with both hands; <as>as, a <ex>two-handed</ex>
sword</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>two-handed</qex> engine [the sword].</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Using either hand equally well;
ambidextrous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Two-lipped</ent>⟦br⟧
